00:05:00.230 --> 00:05:05.000
"can The Matrix be considered
a controlled singularity?"

00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:06.040
Yeah.

00:05:06.040 --> 00:05:10.010
I think The Matrix was presented
as a dystopian meditation

00:05:10.010 --> 00:05:12.680
on control and free
will and identity,

00:05:12.680 --> 00:05:15.290
because dystopian stories
and conflicts make

00:05:15.290 --> 00:05:16.996
more entertaining movies.

00:05:16.996 --> 00:05:21.290
But a lot of stuff that was
hypothesized in that film

00:05:21.290 --> 00:05:23.580
sounds pretty glorious.

00:05:23.580 --> 00:05:26.270
Wouldn't you like to inhabit
a kind of virtual world,

00:05:26.270 --> 00:05:29.600
indistinguishable from
this one, but one in which

00:05:29.600 --> 00:05:32.740
the very physics, the very
constructs of said reality

00:05:32.740 --> 00:05:34.710
are completely malleable?

00:05:34.710 --> 00:05:38.180
Why can't we all be
Neos in The Matrix.

00:05:38.180 --> 00:05:40.450
Why can't we all
move into universes

00:05:40.450 --> 00:05:41.850
of our own construction?

00:05:41.850 --> 00:05:45.190
Terence McKenna says the
man made world is already

00:05:45.190 --> 00:05:46.940
a condensation of
the imagination.

00:05:46.940 --> 00:05:51.970
The whole thing has been
sprouted from the human mind.

00:05:51.970 --> 00:05:56.270
In the film The Matrix, I
didn't see it as a bad thing,

00:05:56.270 --> 00:05:58.660
for us to live in
this virtual utopia.

00:05:58.660 --> 00:06:01.157
But the film found it
necessary to say, oh,

00:06:01.157 --> 00:06:03.365
humans didn't accept the
program when it was perfect.

00:06:03.365 --> 00:06:05.675
They only accepted it when there
was conflict, nah, nah, nah,

00:06:05.675 --> 00:06:07.966
nah, nah, and then it went
off in that other direction.

00:06:07.966 --> 00:06:09.780
But yeah, that's kind
of a singularity.

00:06:09.780 --> 00:06:11.280
The minute you can
create an AI that

00:06:11.280 --> 00:06:14.015
can build a world for
you, that's a singularity.

00:06:14.015 --> 00:06:14.670
Why not?

