That would be awesome.

00:08:26.730 --> 00:08:28.530
"Transcend time
and space, you say.

00:08:28.530 --> 00:08:29.410
This will be fun."

00:08:29.410 --> 00:08:29.910
Well, yeah.

00:08:29.910 --> 00:08:32.150
That's kind of what these
technologies allow us to do.

00:08:32.150 --> 00:08:33.566
Something I've
been thinking about

00:08:33.566 --> 00:08:37.280
lately is how we
use airplanes force

00:08:37.280 --> 00:08:42.289
us to re-accommodate ourselves,
to renegotiate our relationship

00:08:42.289 --> 00:08:44.930
to distance and to
time and to scale.

00:08:44.930 --> 00:08:46.780
What is close and
what is far when it

00:08:46.780 --> 00:08:51.630
takes three hours in traffic
to get from uptown to downtown,

00:08:51.630 --> 00:08:53.300
but then three hours
can also take you

00:08:53.300 --> 00:08:54.830
to another side
of the continent?

00:08:54.830 --> 00:08:58.450
These machines, they transform
all notions of scale,

00:08:58.450 --> 00:09:00.230
all notions of distance.

00:09:00.230 --> 00:09:03.634
But psychologically, it's
still a re-accomodation, right?

00:09:03.634 --> 00:09:05.800
I feel very disjointed when
I take these long trips,

00:09:05.800 --> 00:09:10.690
because there's something
just supernatural, almost,

00:09:10.690 --> 00:09:13.690
about these magical machines
that fly through the sky,

00:09:13.690 --> 00:09:16.340
and we somehow take
it for granted.

00:09:16.340 --> 00:09:18.540
Amber Case, the
cyborg anthropologist,

00:09:18.540 --> 00:09:21.760
says that even right now, here
in a techno-social wormhole,

00:09:21.760 --> 00:09:25.650
we've created this
hole in space and time.

00:09:25.650 --> 00:09:27.910
And wherever you guys
are, you can hear me,

00:09:27.910 --> 00:09:30.100
you can talk to
me, I can hear you.

00:09:30.100 --> 00:09:32.280
The human mind--
at least the part

00:09:32.280 --> 00:09:34.750
of the mind that is
communicating-- communication

00:09:34.750 --> 00:09:36.940
itself between
sentient minds has

00:09:36.940 --> 00:09:38.839
transcended time,
space and distance.

00:09:38.839 --> 00:09:40.005
I think that's unbelievable.

