convince me with

00:13:09.470 --> 00:13:12.850
the deathist rationalization
that says that, oh, death gives

00:13:12.850 --> 00:13:15.470
meaning to life and we would
be bored if we were immortal.

00:13:15.470 --> 00:13:16.150
I'm sorry, man.

00:13:16.150 --> 00:13:18.190
I think that that's just
because we are poetic

00:13:18.190 --> 00:13:20.106
and we've found a way
to accommodate ourselves

00:13:20.106 --> 00:13:21.080
to personal extinction.

00:13:21.080 --> 00:13:23.060
But I [INAUDIBLE] words
of Alan Harrington

00:13:23.060 --> 00:13:25.914
that says, "any philosophy
that accepts death must itself

00:13:25.914 --> 00:13:27.830
be considered dead, its
questions meaningless,

00:13:27.830 --> 00:13:29.540
its consolations worn out."

00:13:29.540 --> 00:13:30.160
I'm sorry.

00:13:30.160 --> 00:13:31.940
Just nobody's going
to convince me

00:13:31.940 --> 00:13:34.760
to accept the
inevitability of loss,

00:13:34.760 --> 00:13:36.975
the inevitability of losing
everyone I care about.

00:13:36.975 --> 00:13:37.850
I just do not accept.

00:13:37.850 --> 00:13:40.030
I just defy those conditions.

00:13:40.030 --> 00:13:42.280
I do not accept those terms.

00:13:42.280 --> 00:13:43.900
I love too much.

00:13:43.900 --> 00:13:45.350
I love my family.

00:13:45.350 --> 00:13:46.690
I love the people in my life.

00:13:46.690 --> 00:13:49.610
And I just don't accept
that this imposition,

00:13:49.610 --> 00:13:53.860
this entropy thing, says oh,
love each other for as long

00:13:53.860 --> 00:13:56.640
as you can, because you're
going to be food for worms.

00:13:56.640 --> 00:13:57.410
Not cool.

00:13:57.410 --> 00:13:59.330
And I think the purpose
of human evolution

00:13:59.330 --> 00:14:00.920
is the trend to end entropy.

00:14:00.920 --> 00:14:03.640
Is to basically engineer
our own divinity.

00:14:03.640 --> 00:14:05.290
That's what it
means to be human.

00:14:05.290 --> 00:14:07.970
To transcend all
previous limits.

00:14:13.870 --> 00:14:16.460
I think we can talk about
anything. [INAUDIBLE] metaphor.

00:14:16.460 --> 00:14:19.150
You can talk about unknowable
things using metaphors.

00:14:19.150 --> 00:14:21.930
Even singularity
is a physics term.

00:14:21.930 --> 00:14:25.180
It's a physics term borrowed
to describe this even horizon,

00:14:25.180 --> 00:14:29.100
this moment in which AI become
smarter than the human brain.

00:14:29.100 --> 00:14:31.350
And so thinking itself
takes on a dimension

00:14:31.350 --> 00:14:34.380
that is unfathomable to human
brains without augmentation.

00:14:34.380 --> 00:14:37.430
The whole idea of it is
that we use language,

00:14:37.430 --> 00:14:41.122
we use poetry to
describe the ineffable.

00:14:41.122 --> 00:14:43.460
That's another great skill
set that we happen to have.

00:14:43.460 --> 00:14:46.390
So I do think we could speculate
about what the singularity--

00:14:46.390 --> 00:14:47.580
how it might play out.

00:14:47.580 --> 00:14:50.520
But sure, to imagine
what it will be like

00:14:50.520 --> 00:14:52.970
is as difficult as trying
to imagine what the world

00:14:52.970 --> 00:14:55.399
post-language would have
been too early hominids

00:14:55.399 --> 00:14:56.690
on the other side of that line.

